The paper focuses on improving stereo matching using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of multi-scale and multi-dimension convolutional neural networks, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on the KITTI dataset, which is a benchmark commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
